<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="257" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1283,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,253,1283,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">Habitus.</emphasis>
Body rounded in dorsal view, strongly convex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[965,1048,1283,1307]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[265,1321,447,1955]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[265,1321,447,1956]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 23. Argopistes rubicundus Blake. 20 dorsal habitus; 21 lateral habitus; 22 head, frontal view; 23 aedeagus, ventral, lateral and dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216668/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
Fig. 
<number box="[1018,1048,1283,1307]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
), almost hemispherical, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.285" metricValueMax="3.36" metricValueMin="3.21" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="3.285" valueMax="3.36" valueMin="3.21">3.21–3.36 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[265,428,1319,1343]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8499999999999996" metricValueMax="2.92" metricValueMin="2.78" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" unit="mm" value="2.8499999999999996" valueMax="2.92" valueMin="2.78">2.78–2.92 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1283,2027]" box="[199,1403,1355,1380]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1355,1380]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">Color.</emphasis>
Entirely dark reddish-brown, with no markings. Antennae and tarsi dark yellowish red (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1391,1355,1379]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[265,1321,447,1955]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[265,1321,447,1956]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 23. Argopistes rubicundus Blake. 20 dorsal habitus; 21 lateral habitus; 22 head, frontal view; 23 aedeagus, ventral, lateral and dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216668/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
Figs 
<number box="[1317,1391,1355,1379]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1283,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1392,1416]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">Head.</emphasis>
Entirely concealed by apical margin of pronotum. Vertex moderately convex, shiny, indistinctly punctate. Antennal calli nearly trapezoidal. Antennal socket about same size as antennal calli. Interantennal space narrower than transverse diameter of antennal socket. Eyes large and oblong, inner margins adjoined to both antennal calli and antennal sockets creating slight emargination along inner margin. Frons generally flattened, separated from each gena by protuberant narrow ridge. Frontal ridge slightly raised extending from interantennal space and reaching clypeus. Genae slightly concave under eyes. Antennae filiform, extending slightly beyond elytral humeri, basal antennomere longest, third antennomere short and slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1283,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1644,1668]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum strongly convex, transverse, twice as broad as long at basal margin. Basal margin arcuate, slightly sinuate. Lateral margins narrowly explanate, strongly converging towards and extending slightly beyond apical margin. Dorsal surface finely and densely punctate. Scutellum small, triangular. Intercoxal prosternal process slightly depressed longitudinally, posterior margin slightly indented, concealing short mesosternum. Metasternum with median longitudinal line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1283,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,1824,1848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">Elytra.</emphasis>
Humeral calli present, but not well developed. Elytral surface densely punctate with confused, minute punctation. Epipleura not reaching apex of elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1283,2027]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,395]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="257" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1896,1920]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256">Legs.</emphasis>
Metafemur generally triangular with rounded corners; length about 
<number box="[1031,1045,1895,1919]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1055,1067,1895,1919]" pageId="7" pageNumber="256" value="3.0">3</number>
length of abdomen; with groove along inner margin. Metatibia longitudinally slightly bowed in dorsal view; about same length as metatarsi combined; with shallow and flat groove at dorsal surface; apex with an emarginate sheath-like prolongation, creating two acutely pointed projections; large pointed spur arises from base of first metatarsomere, and extends between and beyond two acutely pointed projections. First metatarsomere attached to metatibia preapically; at least as long as following three metatarsomeres combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Female—Receptacle of spermatheca elongate, two times larger than pump; ventral and dorsal sides parallel. Pump narrow and elongated; situated almost perpendicular to longitudinal axis of receptacle (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1424,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[265,1320,520,1109]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[265,1321,519,1124]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 26. Argopistes rubicundus Blake. 24 spermatheca; 25 vaginal palpi; 26 tignum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,260,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vaginal palpi about as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[559,643,298,322]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[265,1320,520,1109]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[265,1321,519,1124]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 26. Argopistes rubicundus Blake. 24 spermatheca; 25 vaginal palpi; 26 tignum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">
Fig. 
<number box="[611,643,298,322]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tignum long and narrow, reaching 
<number box="[1053,1067,298,322]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" value="3.0">3</number>
rd visible sternite, basal edge with curved row of setae (
<figureCitation box="[384,468,335,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 26" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[265,1320,520,1109]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[265,1321,519,1124]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 26. Argopistes rubicundus Blake. 24 spermatheca; 25 vaginal palpi; 26 tignum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">
Fig. 
<number box="[436,468,335,359]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male—Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[698,778,335,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[265,1321,447,1955]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[265,1321,447,1956]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 23. Argopistes rubicundus Blake. 20 dorsal habitus; 21 lateral habitus; 22 head, frontal view; 23 aedeagus, ventral, lateral and dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216668/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">
Fig. 
<number box="[749,778,335,359]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) strongly arched in lateral view; widest at basal opening in ventral view, sides parallel and tapering at apex. Ventral side simple without ridges and grooves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216668/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" targetBox="[265,1321,447,1955]" targetPageId="8">
